74.5	Strange_Case_of_Dr_Jekyll_and_Mr_Hyde	Strange Case of Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde	Strange Case of Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde is the original title of a novella written by the Scottish author Robert Louis Stevenson that was first published in 1886. The original pronunciation of Jekyll was "Jeekul" which was the pronunciation used in Stevenson's native Scotland. The work is commonly known today as The Strange Case of Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde, Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde, or simply Jekyll &amp; Hyde. It is about a London lawyer named John Gabriel Utterson who investigates strange occurrences between his old friend, Dr Henry Jekyll, and the misanthropic Edward Hyde.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Jekyll_and_Hyde_Title.jpg/200px-Jekyll_and_Hyde_Title.jpg
